       <div class="wrap">
        <div class="block text-block">
         <h3 class="block-header">
          Congratulations and
          <span>
           Welcome!
          </span>
         </h3>
         <div class="inner">
          <p>
           <span style="font-weight: 400;">
            Congratulations, the entire UC Santa Cruz campus welcomes you and your family to a community of scholars, innovators, risk-takers, and visionary world leaders.
           </span>
          </p>
          <p>
           Slug Orientation is a comprehensive and informational program where you begin to navigate the campus, learn about social and academic resources/programs, prepare for class enrollment, make connections with other students, get your questions answered, have fun, and show your SLUG PRIDE!
          </p>
          <p>
           Welcome to the Banana Slug family!
          </p>
         </div>
        </div>
       </div>
       <div class="wrap last">
        <div class="block text-block">
         <h3 class="block-header">
          Slug
          <span>
           Orientation
          </span>
         </h3>
         <div class="inner">
          <p>
           <strong>
            <span style="font-weight: 400;">
             Slug Orientation is designed to assure you start strong from day one. Slug Orientation
            </span>
           </strong>
           <span style="font-weight: 400;">
            is the next step for all new students, and consists of completing a series of online courses (during June, July and August), meeting deadlines and full participation in Fall Welcome Week.
           </span>
           <span style="font-weight: 400;">
           </span>
          </p>
          <p>
           Slug Orientation Canvas course links will be sent directly to your
           <a href="https://its.ucsc.edu/myucsc-help/applicant-help.html#cruzid">
            UCSC email account
           </a>
           . You will receive individual links for each course (one in June, one in July, and one in August).
          </p>
          <p>
           Learn how to use Canvas by going to
           <a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/0BxgEm3GY5291bWc1ZmlOUGpFMWc/view">
            Getting Started with Canvas
           </a>
           and review the
           <a href="https://its.ucsc.edu/canvas/canvas-faq-student.html">
            Canvas FAQ for Students
           </a>
           .
          </p>
         </div>
        </div>
       </div>
